Travel credit card FAQs

Which travel cards offer bonus miles?

There are several Capital One travel cards that offer the opportunity to earn bonus miles*:

  • Capital One VentureOne Rewards: Earn 20,000 in bonus miles once you spend $500 in the first 3 months. 
  • Capital One Venture Rewards: Earn 75,000 bonus miles once you spend $4,000 in the first 3 months.  
  • Capital One Venture X Rewards: Earn 75,000 bonus miles once you spend $4,000 in the first 3 months. Get 10,000 bonus miles (equal to $100 towards travel) every year, starting on your first anniversary..

*Card offers with a cash or miles rewards bonus are subject to change. See the terms for each offer for the current bonus, if a bonus is available. If offered, the bonus may not be available for existing or previous accountholders.

Which travel card is the best for earning miles?

If you’re looking for a Capital One travel rewards card that will help you earn the most miles, consider the Venture Rewards card or the Venture X Rewards card. 

With Venture Rewards, you can earn 2X miles on everyday purchases, plus even more on hotels and rental cars booked through Capital One Travel.

And with Venture X, you can make your miles go even further. When you book through Capital One Travel, you can get unlimited 5X miles per dollar on flights and 10X miles per dollar on hotels and rental cars, plus 2X miles on every other purchase.

 

 

Is there a travel credit card that offers no annual fee?

Yes, Capital One offers travel rewards credit cards with no annual fee. VentureOne Rewards for Good Credit offers unlimited 1.25 miles on everyday purchases and even more miles on travel booked through Capital One Travel. And with VentureOne Rewards, you can earn miles rewards on everyday purchases and travel, plus 20,000 bonus miles after spending $500 within the first 3 months from account opening.

How do travel credit cards work?

Travel rewards credit cards allow you to earn miles each time you make a qualifying travel or everyday purchase. Once enough miles have accumulated on your account, you can redeem them for travel-related expenses like flights, hotel stays, rentals or vacation packages.

How do travel miles work?

With Capital One travel credit cards, you earn unlimited rewards for every dollar you spend. As you accumulate miles, here are a few ways you can use them:

  • Book a trip with miles through Capital One Travel, or use miles to get reimbursed for recent travel purchases made elsewhere.
  • Use miles to purchase exclusive event tickets on Capital One Entertainment.
  • Book a flight by transferring miles to your choice of travel loyalty programs with partner airlines.
  • Transfer miles to a loved one who also has a Venture card.
  • Redeem miles for cash or gift cards.

Travel miles earned with a Capital One travel credit card don’t expire as long as your account is open and in good standing. There’s also no limit to the number of miles you can earn.

How do I choose the best travel credit card?

The “best” travel credit card for you depends entirely on what you’re looking for. Here are a few questions you can ask to compare your options. 

  • Is there an annual fee?
  • How many miles can I earn, and on which types of purchases?
  • Is there a sign-up bonus?
  • Which travel perks am I most excited about?
     

Are travel credit cards worth it?

Whether or not a travel credit card will be worth it to you will likely depend on how often you travel and how often you plan to use the card each month. Frequent travelers may find that a travel rewards card will provide them with useful benefits and ways to save on travel expenses.

But, for those who travel less frequently, it can be worth exploring other credit card options. A cash back card, for example, may be better suited to fit their needs. Knowing which card option is right for you ultimately comes down to the way you intend to use it.

Annually, eligible Venture X primary account holders will receive a $300 Capital One Travel credit (“Credit”) to use toward purchases made through Capital One Travel. Each annual Credit will expire on the next account open date anniversary. The Credit will be available within Capital One Travel and can be applied to purchases at checkout. The Credit may be used in whole for a single purchase or in part over multiple purchases. Rewards will not be earned on the Credit. If the purchase using the Credit is canceled, the Credit will be restored if it is not expired. An expired Credit will not be restored upon cancellation. A Venture X card account must be open and in good standing to receive or use the Credit.
